{"parentUuid":"3c58e721-4723-41d0-ad8e-10485087fc4c","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"ada254e2f5c7002a8","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TLDv4HqHUuZaoPEU62nBrB","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"small 7B 8B model near zero SWE-bench Verified without scaffolding agentless\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Seed-Coder: Let the Code Model Curate Data for Itself\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2506.03524\"},{\"title\":\"SWE-Dev: Building Software Engineering Agents with ...\",\"url\":\"https://aclanthology.org/2025.findings-acl.193.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Kimi-Dev: Agentless Training as Skill Prior for SWE-Agents\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2509.23045\"},{\"title\":\"SWE-bench Verified (Agentless) Leaderboard\",\"url\":\"https://llm-stats.com/benchmarks/swe-bench-verified-(agentless)\"},{\"title\":\"Kimi-Dev: Agentless Training as Skill Prior for SWE-Agents\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2509.23045v2\"},{\"title\":\"Kimi-Dev: Agentless Training as Skill Prior for SWE-agents | OpenReview\",\"url\":\"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tYppHuGhxJ\"},{\"title\":\"IQuest-Coder-V1 Technical Report\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2603.16733\"},{\"title\":\"SWE-bench Results Viewer\",\"url\":\"https://www.swebench.com/viewer.html\"},{\"title\":\"deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-R1-0528 · Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-R1-0528\"},{\"title\":\"SWE-Fuse: Empowering Software Agents via Issue-free Trajectory Learning and Entropy-aware RLVR Training\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2603.07927v1\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here are the key findings about small 7B/8B models on SWE-bench Verified without scaffolding and with agentless approaches:\n\n## Seed-Coder-8B-Instruct\n\nSeed-Coder-8B-Instruct achieves the strongest performance among all ~8B models on SWE-bench Verified with a 19.2% resolved rate under Agentless. Despite its smaller size, it matches or exceeds the performance of much larger models such as QwQ-32B (18.4%) and Qwen2.5-Coder-14B-Instruct (19.4%).\n\n## Qwen2.5-Coder-7B\n\nQwen2.5-Coder-7B achieves 18.2% resolved rate on SWE-bench Verified with the Agentless approach.\n\n## Key Observations\n\nAgentless outperforms agent-based methods in most cases because smaller models typically rely on pre-defined workflows (Agentless) to perform reliably and often fail when required to operate autonomously.\n\nThe search results show that among small models (7B-8B range), Seed-Coder-8B-Instruct is currently the leading performer on SWE-bench Verified when using the agentless approach without additional scaffolding.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"4b3d669a-97ea-4f57-8e69-93873778fe30","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:48.513Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"small 7B 8B model near zero SWE-bench Verified without scaffolding agentless","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01GCHA6b7VigME89ncAnPAuN","content":[{"title":"Seed-Coder: Let the Code Model Curate Data for Itself","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2506.03524"},{"title":"SWE-Dev: Building Software Engineering Agents with ...","url":"https://aclanthology.org/2025.findings-acl.193.pdf"},{"title":"Kimi-Dev: Agentless Training as Skill Prior for SWE-Agents","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2509.23045"},{"title":"SWE-bench Verified (Agentless) Leaderboard","url":"https://llm-stats.com/benchmarks/swe-bench-verified-(agentless)"},{"title":"Kimi-Dev: Agentless Training as Skill Prior for SWE-Agents","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2509.23045v2"},{"title":"Kimi-Dev: Agentless Training as Skill Prior for SWE-agents | OpenReview","url":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tYppHuGhxJ"},{"title":"IQuest-Coder-V1 Technical Report","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2603.16733"},{"title":"SWE-bench Results Viewer","url":"https://www.swebench.com/viewer.html"},{"title":"deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-R1-0528 · Hugging Face","url":"https://huggingface.co/deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-R1-0528"},{"title":"SWE-Fuse: Empowering Software Agents via Issue-free Trajectory Learning and Entropy-aware RLVR Training","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2603.07927v1"}]},"Based on the search results, here are the key findings about small 7B/8B models on SWE-bench Verified without scaffolding and with agentless approaches:\n\n## Seed-Coder-8B-Instruct\n\nSeed-Coder-8B-Instruct achieves the strongest performance among all ~8B models on SWE-bench Verified with a 19.2% resolved rate under Agentless. Despite its smaller size, it matches or exceeds the performance of much larger models such as QwQ-32B (18.4%) and Qwen2.5-Coder-14B-Instruct (19.4%).\n\n## Qwen2.5-Coder-7B\n\nQwen2.5-Coder-7B achieves 18.2% resolved rate on SWE-bench Verified with the Agentless approach.\n\n## Key Observations\n\nAgentless outperforms agent-based methods in most cases because smaller models typically rely on pre-defined workflows (Agentless) to perform reliably and often fail when required to operate autonomously.\n\nThe search results show that among small models (7B-8B range), Seed-Coder-8B-Instruct is currently the leading performer on SWE-bench Verified when using the agentless approach without additional scaffolding."],"durationSeconds":6.407590874999761,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"3c58e721-4723-41d0-ad8e-10485087fc4c","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
