{"parentUuid":"6de53ff7-8382-4529-9499-c878a67a8b32","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"ada254e2f5c7002a8","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014a3xzarok19oAmDjNDfnYE","type":"tool_result","content":"# Qwen2.5-Coder Benchmark Scores\n\nBased on the blog post, here are the reported metrics:\n\n## Specific Benchmark Scores\n\nThe document does not provide exact numerical scores for HumanEval or MBPP for individual model sizes (7B, 14B, 32B). \n\nFor **LiveCodeBench**, the post states the Instruct models were \"evaluated\" using \"the latest 4 months of LiveCodeBench (2024.07 - 2024.11)\" but no specific scores per model size are given.\n\nFor **Aider (code repair)**, only the 32B model score is mentioned: \"Qwen2.5-Coder-32B-Instruct scored 73.7, performing comparably to GPT-4o on Aider.\"\n\n## SWE-bench\n\n**No, SWE-bench is not mentioned** in this document.\n\n## Visual Performance Data\n\nThe post includes charts showing comparative performance across model sizes on various benchmarks, but the exact numerical values per model are not transcribed in the text. The document emphasizes that \"There is a positive correlation between model size and model performance\" and that Qwen2.5-Coder achieved \"SOTA performance across all sizes,\" but granular benchmark scores for each model tier are not explicitly stated in readable text format."}]},"uuid":"06a948bc-89bb-4673-b12d-013f67906f17","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:17.176Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":37224,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Qwen2.5-Coder Benchmark Scores\n\nBased on the blog post, here are the reported metrics:\n\n## Specific Benchmark Scores\n\nThe document does not provide exact numerical scores for HumanEval or MBPP for individual model sizes (7B, 14B, 32B). \n\nFor **LiveCodeBench**, the post states the Instruct models were \"evaluated\" using \"the latest 4 months of LiveCodeBench (2024.07 - 2024.11)\" but no specific scores per model size are given.\n\nFor **Aider (code repair)**, only the 32B model score is mentioned: \"Qwen2.5-Coder-32B-Instruct scored 73.7, performing comparably to GPT-4o on Aider.\"\n\n## SWE-bench\n\n**No, SWE-bench is not mentioned** in this document.\n\n## Visual Performance Data\n\nThe post includes charts showing comparative performance across model sizes on various benchmarks, but the exact numerical values per model are not transcribed in the text. The document emphasizes that \"There is a positive correlation between model size and model performance\" and that Qwen2.5-Coder achieved \"SOTA performance across all sizes,\" but granular benchmark scores for each model tier are not explicitly stated in readable text format.","durationMs":5001,"url":"https://qwenlm.github.io/blog/qwen2.5-coder-family/"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"6de53ff7-8382-4529-9499-c878a67a8b32","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"9fb85cc3-c193-4b05-9730-1eef8a950d59","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"ada254e2f5c7002a8","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016hKjULQLQxckkaYGpHUjyT","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Qwen3-8B model card LiveCodeBench code benchmark score not coder\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Qwen 3 Benchmarks, Comparisons, Model Specifications, and More - DEV Community\",\"url\":\"https://dev.to/best_codes/qwen-3-benchmarks-comparisons-model-specifications-and-more-4hoa\"},{\"title\":\"LiveCodeBench Leaderboard - Holistic and Contamination Free Evaluation\",\"url\":\"https://livecodebench.github.io/leaderboard.html\"},{\"title\":\"LiveCodeBench v6 Leaderboard\",\"url\":\"https://llm-stats.com/benchmarks/livecodebench-v6\"},{\"title\":\"LiveCodeBench v6 Benchmark\",\"url\":\"https://www.emergentmind.com/topics/livecodebench-v6\"},{\"title\":\"Qwen3 Technical Report\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2505.09388v1\"},{\"title\":\"Qwen/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B · Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B\"},{\"title\":\"Qwen3: Think Deeper, Act Faster | Qwen\",\"url\":\"https://qwenlm.github.io/blog/qwen3/\"},{\"title\":\"LiveCodeBench Leaderboard 2026 - Compare AI Model Scores\",\"url\":\"https://pricepertoken.com/leaderboards/benchmark/livecodebench\"},{\"title\":\"Qwen3.6-35B-A3B: Agentic Coding Power, Now Open to All\",\"url\":\"https://qwen.ai/blog?id=qwen3.6-35b-a3b\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found information about Qwen3 model performance on LiveCodeBench, though the specific Qwen3-8B model's score isn't prominently featured. Here's what I found:\n\n## Qwen3 Series and LiveCodeBench Performance\n\nThe Qwen3 series includes 6 dense models, namely Qwen3-0.6B, Qwen3-1.7B, Qwen3-4B, Qwen3-8B, Qwen3-14B, and Qwen3-32B, and 2 MoE models, Qwen3-30B-A3B and Qwen3-235B-A22B.\n\nFor LiveCodeBench performance:\n- The flagship model Qwen3-235B-A22B achieves 70.7 on LiveCodeBench v5\n- All Qwen3 8B / 4B / 1.7B / 0.6B-Base models continue to maintain strong performance across nearly all benchmarks.\n- Notably, Qwen3-8B / 4B / 1.7B-Base models even outperform larger size Qwen2.5-14B / 7B / 3B Base models on over half of the benchmarks, especially on STEM-related tasks.\n\nWhile the search results don't provide the specific LiveCodeBench numeric score for the Qwen3-8B model alone, they indicate that the Qwen3-8B base model performs competitively relative to other models in its size class and outperforms larger previous generation models on coding and STEM benchmarks.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"358f5f07-c0d5-4d04-8931-5a86117f8a1f","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:20.454Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"Qwen3-8B model card LiveCodeBench code benchmark score not coder","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01MjLGh9Bd6NeYboCEvGBrva","content":[{"title":"Qwen 3 Benchmarks, Comparisons, Model Specifications, and More - DEV Community","url":"https://dev.to/best_codes/qwen-3-benchmarks-comparisons-model-specifications-and-more-4hoa"},{"title":"LiveCodeBench Leaderboard - Holistic and Contamination Free Evaluation","url":"https://livecodebench.github.io/leaderboard.html"},{"title":"LiveCodeBench v6 Leaderboard","url":"https://llm-stats.com/benchmarks/livecodebench-v6"},{"title":"LiveCodeBench v6 Benchmark","url":"https://www.emergentmind.com/topics/livecodebench-v6"},{"title":"Qwen3 Technical Report","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2505.09388v1"},{"title":"Qwen/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B · Hugging Face","url":"https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B"},{"title":"Qwen3: Think Deeper, Act Faster | Qwen","url":"https://qwenlm.github.io/blog/qwen3/"},{"title":"LiveCodeBench Leaderboard 2026 - Compare AI Model Scores","url":"https://pricepertoken.com/leaderboards/benchmark/livecodebench"},{"title":"Qwen3.6-35B-A3B: Agentic Coding Power, Now Open